</div>

<p>It will cause the browser to make four requests in order to understand the page's layout. The code snipet bellow belongs to the example using LightningPacker.</p>

<div class="html">
<?php

echo htmlentities('<head>
<title>Example of Page with LightningPacker</title>
<link rel="shortcut icon" href="/img/example/favicon.ico" type="image/x-icon" />
<?= lightningPacker(array("http://lightningpacker.net/css/810.css", "http://lightningpacker.net/css/example.css", "http://lightningpacker.net/css/example-simplemodal.css", "http://lightningpacker.net/css/jquery.jqzoom.css"), "css"); ?>;
</head>');
?>

</div>

<p>In terms of CSS, both approaches have the exactly same effect. The difference is the number of requests performed and the amount of data tranfered.</p>

